# GreenEyes NYC — Cursor Rules

## Project Context
This is a full-stack React + Node.js project for a NYC energy reduction monitoring platform.
It is a 6-page marketing/product website with a live dashboard.

## Stack
- Frontend: React 18, Vite, Tailwind CSS v3, Recharts, Axios
- Backend: Express, better-sqlite3 (SQLite), Node.js
- No TypeScript (plain JS/JSX)

## Code Style
- Use functional React components with hooks only (no class components)
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes for all styling (no inline styles except for dynamic values)
- Use `const` for all variables and function declarations
- No semicolons unless necessary
- 2-space indentation
- Single quotes for strings

## Architecture Rules
- All API calls live in `frontend/src/api/*.js` files
- All API files must include mock data fallbacks (safeFetch pattern)
- Dashboard widgets live in `frontend/src/components/dashboard/`
- Reusable UI primitives live in `frontend/src/components/ui/`
- Each of the 6 pages lives in `frontend/src/components/pages/`
- Backend routes live in `backend/routes/` — one file per resource
- Database schema is managed in `backend/db/database.js`
- Seed data lives in `backend/db/seed.js`

## Design System
- Primary green: `#22c55e` (grass green)
- Dark green: `#16a34a`
- Light green: `#4ade80`
- Neutral blue circles: `#64b5f6`
- Blueprint navy: `#0f2942`
- Blueprint line: `#4a9fd4`
- Light gray-blue bg: `#e8edf2` to `#cde0e8` gradient
- Dashboard bg: `#020917` to `#0a0f1e`

## Database Tables
buildings, ll97_limits, compliance_snapshots, energy_readings, solar_readings, alerts, sensors, floors, users, user_buildings

## API Endpoints
GET /api/buildings, /api/buildings/:id, /api/buildings/:id/ll97, /api/buildings/:id/compliance
GET /api/energy/:id, /api/energy/:id/current, /api/energy/:id/floors
GET /api/solar/:id, /api/solar/:id/performance
GET /api/alerts/:id, /api/alerts/:id/count
PATCH /api/alerts/:id/resolve
GET /api/sensors/:id, /api/sensors/:id/status
PATCH /api/sensors/:id/heartbeat
GET /api/health

## When adding new features
1. Add the DB table/column to `backend/db/database.js` initSchema
2. Add seed data to `backend/db/seed.js`
3. Add route to `backend/routes/` and register in `backend/server.js`
4. Add API function to `frontend/src/api/` with mock fallback
5. Create component in appropriate `components/` subfolder
6. Import and use in the relevant Page component

